citation.case_name: Jones v. Jackson, Judge, United States District Court for the District of Columbia

html:
510 U.S. 962

Jones
v.
Jackson, Judge, United States District Court for the District of Columbia, et al.

No. 93-5622.

Supreme Court of United States.

November 8, 1993.

1

Appeal from the C. A. D. C. Cir.

2

Motion of petitioner for reconsideration of order denying leave to proceed in forma pauperis [ante, p. 808] denied. Justice GINSBURG took no part in the consideration or decision of this motion.
